snippet: After losing their way a few years ago, both Tiger Woods and Wall Street have both rebounded to success. But, in each case, how long will it last?
abstract: Jeff Sommer Strategies column observes that after a long run of spectacular fortune, both the stock market and Tiger Woods lost their way several years ago; points out, however, that in March, Woods won a golf tournament, and the Standard & Poor's 500 closed above 1,400, 107 percent above its 2009 low; wonders how long each success will last.
lead_paragraph: After losing their way a few years ago, both Tiger Woods and Wall Street have both rebounded to success. But, in each case, how long will it last?

headline.print_headline: Tiger and the Stock Market, Together Again
headline.seo: Stock Market, Like Tiger Woods, Is Out of the Rough
headline.main: Tiger and the Stock Market, Together Again
